  "time_ut": 1655904720,
  "title": "DFCC Bank commemorates World Bicycle Day in line with its sustainability strategy",
  "body_lines": [
    "The Bank for Everyone, and one of the pioneers in the Banking industry to embracecycling, DFCC Bank celebrated World Bicycle Dayrecently.WorldBicycle Day falls on 3rd June each year and draws attention to the various health and environmental benefits of cycling; a simple, affordable, clean and environmentally friendly means of transportation. To commemorate this day, the Bank took the opportunity to declare it a \u201cBike to Work\u201d day for its employees, and organised a 15 Km fun ride for which over 30 cyclists participated.",
    "In addition, DFCC Bank also conducted a special knowledge sharing session focusing on topics in relation to cycling etiquette, safety measures, benefits of cycling to work, selection of the ideal bike etc.,which saw enthusiastic participation by the staff.",
    "\u201cEXERCISE\u201d is one of the key pillars of the Bank\u2019s sustainability strategy, and one of the Bank\u2019s flagship initiatives under this pillar is to promote cycling as a lifestyle among staff, customers and other stakeholders.",
    "Further, DFCC was one of the pioneers to launch the Monthly Cycling Day initiative in 2020, to coincide with the opening of the new Pinnacle Centre in Horton place for which participants included customers, well-wishers and employees of the Bank. Since this modest inception, the initiative has grown into a network-wide effort to promote cycling to work and cycling as a lifestyle, which now attracts and appeals to many hundreds of the Bank\u2019s employees. An increase in participation and interest is now also being witnessed across DFCC Bank\u2019s branches in the Central, Northern, Eastern and Southern regions as well.",
    "DFCC Bank\u2019s Monthly Cycle Days are organized by the Bank\u2019s Wellness (OMMM) Committee, and Human Resources Department, with the support and participation of senior members of the management, including the CEO, Thimal Perera, and many others. To support cycling as a lifestyle and promote the activity amongst its people, the Bank has issued branded jerseys and introduced financial support programmesfor employees to purchase bicycles as well.",
    "Marginal rise in CSE trading; PM\u2019s statement positively impacts bourse",
